text:
William Benner Enright (July 12, 1925 – March 7, 2020) was a Senior United States District Judge of the United States District Court for the Southern District of California. He was born in New York City. In 1972, he was nominated to the court by President Richard Nixon.
Enright died on March 7, 2020 in San Diego, California, aged 94.
